  "algorithm_summary": "This Type 1 Diabetes phenotype algorithm identifies cases by requiring both a T1D diagnosis (ICD-9: 250._1*, 250._3*; ICD-10: E10*) AND insulin prescription, then excludes patients with T2D medications, malignant cancer (4+ diagnoses), cystic fibrosis, or drug-induced diabetes. Controls must be age >4 with 2+ diagnoses 2+ years apart, excluding any diabetes diagnoses, diabetes medications, cancer, or cystic fibrosis. The algorithm incorporates genetic risk scoring using both GRS (genetic risk score) and PRS (polygenic risk score) models developed in European populations, achieving ROC AUC of 0.903 when combined.",
